# 📌 Introduction

Microsoft Windows Hardening is the process of securing a Windows operating system by reducing its attack surface, enforcing strict access controls, disabling unnecessary services, and applying security best practices.

This report consolidates all major hardening areas into a **single structured document**, covering:

- Identity & Access Management  
- Network Management  
- Application Management  
- Storage & Compute Security  
- Importance of Updating Windows  
- Windows Hardening Cheat Sheet  

The objective is to create a **secure baseline configuration** suitable for enterprise and SOC environments.

